Dominique Strauss-Kahn , the head of
the International Monetary Fund, was arrested today at John F.
Kennedy International Airport after being accused earlier of a
sexual attack, the New York Times reported.  Strauss-Kahn was on a flight to Paris, and was taken off
the plane by  Port Authority  of New York and New Jersey officers,
the Times said. He was turned over to New York detectives.  The newspaper said he was accused of an attack on a maid at
a Times Square hotel earlier in the day.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at 
